document_data.Worshipers:
The priests of his faith were permitted to wield any kind of weapon, so long as it was made of metal. They wore a kilt as part of their priestly vestments. They had access to spells from the [[all sphere|all]], [[animal sphere|animal]], [[astral sphere|astral]], [[charm sphere|charm]], [[combat sphere|combat]], [[creation sphere|creation]], [[elemental sphere|elemental]], [[guardian sphere|guardian]], [[healing sphere|healing]], [[protection sphere|protection]], [[sun sphere|sun]], and [[weather sphere|weather]] [[sphere]]s. They particularly had access to the spell ''[[heroes' feast]]''. They also were capable of enchanting any weapon, shield, or suit of armor with a ''+2 [[item enchantment|enchantment]].''

His priests were required to watch over and protect both smiths and [[warrior]]s, as well as oversee the feeding and healing of the faithful. They were often proficient in blacksmithing, serving as a royal court's armorer or blacksmith.

